<paragraph blockId="3.[151,923,1049,1071]" box="[151,923,1049,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Cerf, 1922" authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[294,672,1049,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[294,523,1049,1070]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Malgassesia rufescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[529,672,1049,1071]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref6943" refString="Le Cerf, F. (1922) Troisieme Contribution a l'etude des Aegeriidae. Descriptions d'Especes et Varietes nouvelles. Etudes de Lepidopterologie Comparee, 19 (2), 17 - 39, 190 - 191, pls. 539 - 540." type="journal article">Le Cerf, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1116,2005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
In the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[491,631,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[491,631,1116,1141]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Malgassesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[679,852,1116,1141]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref6943" refString="Le Cerf, F. (1922) Troisieme Contribution a l'etude des Aegeriidae. Descriptions d'Especes et Varietes nouvelles. Etudes de Lepidopterologie Comparee, 19 (2), 17 - 39, 190 - 191, pls. 539 - 540." type="journal article">Le Cerf (1922)</bibRefCitation>
only a single species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[1117,1263,1116,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[1117,1263,1116,1140]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was included. Later, 
<bibRefCitation box="[224,385,1151,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7221" refString="Viette, P. ([1955]) Nouveaux Tineoidea (s. l.) de Madagascar [Lep.]. Famille Aegeriidae. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 123 (1954), 87 - 95." type="journal article">Viette ([1955]</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[398,457,1151,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7265" refString="Viette, P. (1957) Deux nouvelles Sesies de Madagascar (Lep. Aegeriidae). Le Naturaliste Malgache, 9 (1), 91 - 94." type="journal article">1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[469,527,1152,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7296" refString="Viette, P. (1982) Insectes Lepidopteres Sesiidae. Faune de Madagascar, 61, 1 - 64." type="journal article">1982</bibRefCitation>
) assigned five more species to the genus. Two of them, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[1168,1348,1151,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biedermanni">
<emphasis box="[1168,1348,1151,1176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. biedermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette, [" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauliani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. pauliani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are discussed in detail below. The remaining three, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1957" box="[859,1038,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankaratralis">
<emphasis box="[859,1038,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. ankaratralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[1054,1168,1188,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milloti">
<emphasis box="[1054,1168,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. milloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" box="[1228,1344,1189,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Tipulamima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis box="[1228,1344,1189,1212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, appear exceptionally heterogeneous and a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[830,978,1224,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[830,978,1224,1248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is questionable. The following striking differences are noted in comparison to the type species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[804,951,1260,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[804,951,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" box="[969,1086,1261,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Tipulamima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis box="[969,1086,1261,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the male antenna slightly clavate, distally gradually broadened, dorsally with white subapical spot (narrower, less distinctly clubbed, without white spot in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[306,450,1332,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[306,450,1332,1356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the body long and slender (shorter and stronger in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[1050,1194,1332,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[1050,1194,1332,1356]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the forewing discal spot and apical area broad (narrow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[573,716,1368,1392]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[573,716,1368,1392]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the hindwing discal spot very small (largest of the group in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The holotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" box="[472,584,1404,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milloti">
<emphasis box="[472,584,1404,1429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. milloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
misses the antennae; it has the body long and slender; the forewing discal spot and apical area very narrow; the hindwing discal spot absent; the wings, particularly the hindwing tornus, and the transparent areas broadest of the group. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1957" box="[655,833,1476,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankaratralis">
<emphasis box="[655,833,1476,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. ankaratralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the male antenna long and narrow, very slightly clavate, without white spot; the body long and very slender; the forewing discal spot and apical area broad; the hindwing discal spot very small. It is further the only nocturnal 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[871,1047,1548,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
of Madagascar (
<bibRefCitation box="[1236,1372,1548,1573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7296" refString="Viette, P. (1982) Insectes Lepidopteres Sesiidae. Faune de Madagascar, 61, 1 - 64." type="journal article">Viette 1982</bibRefCitation>
). The male genitalia in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1957" box="[362,543,1583,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankaratralis">
<emphasis box="[362,543,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. ankaratralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with valva very long, narrow, apically pointed, without crista sacculi (not elongated, apically rounded, crista sacculi well developed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[860,1007,1620,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufescens">
<emphasis box="[860,1007,1620,1644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. rufescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" box="[1228,1344,1621,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Tipulamima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis box="[1228,1344,1621,1644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. seyrigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milloti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. milloti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not known. The relationship of three further species, which were originally described in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spuler" authorityYear="1910" box="[1257,1436,1655,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chamaesphecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1436,1655,1680]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Chamaesphecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later excluded from this genus as “incertae sedis” (
<bibRefCitation box="[763,1057,1692,1717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7027" refString="Puhringer, F. &amp; Kallies, A. (2004) Provisional checklist of the Sesiidae of the world (Lepidoptera: Ditrysia). Mitteilungen der Entomologischen Arbeitsgemeinschaft Salzkammergut, 4, 185." type="journal article">Pühringer &amp; Kallies 2004</bibRefCitation>
), could not yet be clarified. These species are here transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[504,644,1727,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[504,644,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Malgassesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Viette, 1982)" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Viette" baseAuthorityYear="1982" box="[661,998,1727,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andrianony" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[661,830,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. andrianony</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[847,989,1727,1752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref7296" refString="Viette, P. (1982) Insectes Lepidopteres Sesiidae. Faune de Madagascar, 61, 1 - 64." type="journal article">Viette, 1982</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1007,1138,1727,1752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1138,1727,1752]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[1155,1259,1727,1752]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1789,1812]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1741]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1765]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Adult specimens of Madagascan Synanthedonini: 1–5. Rodolphia hombergi Le Cerf, 1911. (1–2) male, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (4–5) female, same data. (3) male, holotype of Malgassesia pauliani Viette, 1955, ventral view. 6–7. Malgassesia andrianony (Viette, 1982) comb. nov., male holotype. 8–12. Malgassesia rufescens Le Cerf, 1922. (8–9) male, Madagascar, Ihosy, Region sud de l’Ile. (10–11) female, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (12) female, holotype of Malgassesia biedermanni Viette, 1982. Scale bars 10 mm, ventral view right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1287075/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName authority="(Le Cerf, 1957)" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Le Cerf" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lemur" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1283,1387,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. lemur</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref6988" refString="Le Cerf, F. (1957) Nouveaux genres et especes d'Aegeriidae de Madagascar [Lep.]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 62 (3 - 4), 97 - 100." type="journal article">Le Cerf, 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[301,437,1764,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[301,437,1764,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[458,596,1764,1789]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,223,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Adult specimens of Madagascan Synanthedonini: 13–14. Malgassesia lemur (Le Cerf, 1957) comb. nov., male holotype. 15–16. Malgassesia ferdinandi nom. nov., male holotype. 17–19. Epitarsipus rufithorax Le Cerf, 1922 comb. rev. (17–18) male, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (19) female, same data. 20–22. Cinctosesia polistiformis sp. nov. (20–21) male holotype (freshly emerged specimen). (22) male paratype (older specimen). 23–24. Nesosphecia mystica sp. nov., male holotype. Scale bars 10 mm, ventral view right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1287077/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
); and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" box="[678,838,1764,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferdinandi" status="nom. nov.">
<emphasis box="[678,838,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. ferdinandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[852,975,1764,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[852,975,1764,1789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">nom. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, (in honour of Ferdinand Le Cerf), a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Le Cerf, 1957" authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1957" box="[402,827,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chamaesphecia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seyrigi">
<emphasis box="[402,664,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Chamaesphecia seyrigi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[670,827,1799,1824]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" refId="ref6988" refString="Le Cerf, F. (1957) Nouveaux genres et especes d'Aegeriidae de Madagascar [Lep.]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 62 (3 - 4), 97 - 100." type="journal article">Le Cerf, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[842,972,1799,1824]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1784,1807]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,223,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1763]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13–24. Adult specimens of Madagascan Synanthedonini: 13–14. Malgassesia lemur (Le Cerf, 1957) comb. nov., male holotype. 15–16. Malgassesia ferdinandi nom. nov., male holotype. 17–19. Epitarsipus rufithorax Le Cerf, 1922 comb. rev. (17–18) male, Madagascar, Bekily, Region sud de l’Ile. (19) female, same data. 20–22. Cinctosesia polistiformis sp. nov. (20–21) male holotype (freshly emerged specimen). (22) male paratype (older specimen). 23–24. Nesosphecia mystica sp. nov., male holotype. Scale bars 10 mm, ventral view right." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1287077/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Figs 15–16</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2018" box="[992,1145,1799,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferdinandi">
<emphasis box="[992,1145,1799,1824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">M. ferdinandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs considerably from all other African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[346,525,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
, in particular by the coloration of abdomen and forewings, and may well belong to a separate genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1116,2005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">
In its current form 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[435,575,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[435,575,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Malgassesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is certainly paraphyletic and represents the melting pot of Madagascan 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,330,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
, which could not be assigned to genus. However, detailed examination of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Cerf" authorityYear="1922" box="[1178,1318,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Malgassesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1178,1318,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="177">Malgassesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is beyond the scope of this study and will have to await a broader phylogenetic analysis of the African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Niculescu" authorityYear="1964" box="[1187,1366,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synanthedonini">Synanthedonini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
